title: Tintin artwork sells for record-breaking £1.9m
description: A black and white Tintin drawing has sold at auction for more than €2.m (£1.9m).

title: US-made F-16s are the 'optimal choice' of jets, says Ukrainian fighter pilot
description: A Ukrainian fighter pilot said he would be happy to fly a British Typhoon jet but he does not know how realistic that would be given how expensive and limited in number they are.

title: US-made F-16s are the 'optimal choice' of jets, says Ukrainian fighter pilot
description: A Ukrainian fighter pilot said he would be happy to fly a British Typhoon jet but he does not know how realistic that would be given how expensive and limited in number they are.

title: US shoots down unknown object flying in airspace near Alaska
description: The US has shot down an unknown object flying in its airspace, off the coastline of Alaska - just days after it downed a Chinese "spy" balloon.

title: The laws Putin has broken - and how he alone is responsible for Russia's fall from glory
description: President Putin aspired to make Russia "great" again - but with his unprovoked invasion of Ukraine he has ignored the key protocols designed to keep people safe and maintain honour in battle.

title: Indian govt withdraws appeal to hug cows on Valentine's Day after criticism
description: Hugging a cow on Valentine's Day is no longer being encouraged by the Indian government - despite it previously asking people to do so to promote Hindu values.

title: Man who lost nine relatives in quake helps organise UK aid - as community groups flooded with donations
description: A man helping sort aid for the Turkey earthquake says nine of his relatives died in the disaster but has praised the community response - as UK groups urgently drive collections for survivors.

title: Group of 35 countries 'back ban' on Russian and Belarusian athletes at Paris Olympics
description: A group of 35 countries are to demand that Russian and Belarusian athletes are banned from the 2024 Olympics over Vladimir Putin's invasion of Ukraine, according to Lithuania's sports minister.

title: Inside Syria: Rebel leader calls for urgent international help as families devastated by quake
description: Syria's suffering is a unique desolation and inside Idlib we've seen the face of utter desperation.

title: Two killed, including six-year-old boy, after car driven into crowd at Jerusalem bus stop
description: Two people, including a six-year-old boy, have been killed after a car was driven into a group of people at a bus stop on the outskirts of Jerusalem.

title: Woman tried to kill beautician with poisoned cheesecake to steal her identity
description: A woman has been convicted of trying to kill a beautician with poisoned cheesecake in order to steal her identity.

title: 'We thought they were dead': Sisters rescued minutes apart
description: The air is filled with dust and smoke, the city marked with heaps of rubble - but there is evidence of life in Kahramanmaras.

title: Dog breeder shot and killed while trying to sell French bulldog
description: A dog breeder was shot and killed on Monday night after a planned sale of a French bulldog went wrong, police have said.

title: Amsterdam to weed out cannabis in red light district
description: Amsterdam will ban smoking cannabis in public in the city's red light district to reduce the "enormous nuisance" affecting residents.

title: Trapped for 100 hours: A newborn baby, a family of six and a teenager among those saved from under rubble
description: A newborn baby and a family of six are among those to defy the odds and be pulled alive from the rubble in Turkey days after the devastating earthquake.

title: Air raid alert in force across Ukraine as Russia steps up attacks
description: An air raid alert has been declared across the whole of Ukraine as Russia launched strikes in the country's south and east.

title: Teenage girl who was missing for more than a year found alive in wardrobe
description: A 14-year-old girl who was reported missing in  2021 has been found pregnant in the closet of a Michigan home.

title: Zelenskyy to discuss Russia's involvement in Paris Olympics as Ukraine threatens to boycott
description: Ukraine's president will address a summit on Friday to discuss Russia's participation in next year's Paris Olympics following warnings his country could boycott the Games.

title: UK sends thousands of thermal blankets to Turkey - and will build field hospital in days to come
description: The UK has sent thousands of thermal blankets to Turkey - and is planning to build a field hospital to treat those critically injured after Monday's devastating earthquake.
